cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a new method for evaluating scientific literature based on article-level metrics, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, management, and access to digital information, including scholarly literature. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information from large collections of documents. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the proposed method aims to quantify both academic and societal impact. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the proposed method could potentially be applied to analyze the impact of scientific literature on social networks. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still relevant as the proposed method could potentially be used to evaluate the impact of research on security and privacy.
